org.opendatakit.aggregate.odktables.rest.entity

Class Column

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opendatakit.aggregate.odktables.rest.entity.Column
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Column
extends Object
implements Serializable
    The XML document that represents a column. This is the XML representation of a column definition as stored in the (keep this fully qualified!) org.opendatakit.aggregate.odktables.relation.DbColumnDefinitions table. Removed all JAXB annotations -- these cause issues on Android 4.2 and earlier.
    Author:
    dylan price?, sudar.sam@gmail.com

        public Column(String elementKey,
              String elementName,

        Create a column. NB: It needs to be decided if backing name and display name are different in the datastore on the server in the same way they are on the phone, and if they should both be stored in the COLUMN table as adjacent columns, or what exactly. Either way, its implementation should be brought into alignment with ColumnClient, which has both display and backing names when the answer to the above questions is decided.
        Parameters:
        tableId -
        elementKey -
        elementName -
        elementType -
        listChildElementKeys - - a JSON serialization of a list of child elementKey values. These must be in the (alphabetical) order produced by Javascript sort().
